data.body: [{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Dry & Hot Most Of This Week","forecastDesc":"Excessive Heat Warning to start the week. Some dangerous heat will build in early in the week with high humidity.  If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in this area the weather pattern is setting up for a calmer and drier week. Weather 2020 uses the LRC, the cycling pattern, to make these accurate forecasts, and this week there will likely be a strong cold front approaching by the weekend.  If you are in Omaha, Des Moines, St. Louis, Kansas City, Springfield, Branson, Topeka, Wichita, and Dodge City, there will be a good chance of thunderstorms with this front with the rest of the week staying hot and mostly dry.  If you are out on the lake this week, keep an eye to the sky. There will likely be a  few isolated thunderstorms with a slight chance of a microburst wind near these thunderstorms. Go to Weather2020.com, enter our long range forecasting contest with a monthly winner of a $100 Visa Gift Card, and join the LRC Forecast Experience blog to learn more about this breakthrough technology.","startDate":1436659200,"revision":6,"events":[],"conditions":[{"tag":"thunderstorm","display":"Thunderstorm"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":93,"temperatureLow":74,"temperatureHighCelcius":34,"temperatureLowCelcius":23},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Thunderstorm Chances","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in this area, there will be three to four days with a chance of thunderstorms. The weather pattern this week will see a cold front heading south and perhaps stalling as a series of smaller systems track out of the Rockies. This has the potential to be a wet set-up this week. If the front can push south out of this region, more days this week will see spectacular summer weather. Temperatures this week will run mostly below average.  Check back for updates if you plan to be in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Springfield, Columbia, St. Louis, Lake of the Ozarks, Branson, Des Moines, Omaha, Lincoln, or Grand Island as we see how far south this front will track.  Go to Weather2020.com, enter our long range forecasting contest with a monthly winner of a $100 Visa Gift Card, and join the LRC Forecast Experience blog to learn more about this breakthrough technology.","startDate":1437264000,"revision":4,"events":[],"conditions":[{"tag":"thunderstorm","display":"Thunderstorm"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":84,"temperatureLow":64,"temperatureHighCelcius":29,"temperatureLowCelcius":18},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Chance of a Thunderstorm","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Springfield, Columbia, St. Louis, Des Moines, or Omaha, there will be two to three days with a chance of thunderstorms. These chances will be coming from one or two weak cold fronts and possibly one system dropping in from the northwest. Most of the days will be dry, very warm, and humid (temperatures near average), typical for the end of July in these locations.  This looks like a good week to head to the Lake of the Ozarks or Branson, just keep an eye to the sky.  Go to Weather2020.com, enter our long range forecasting contest with a monthly winner of a $100 Visa Gift Card, and join the LRC Forecast Experience blog to learn more about this breakthrough technology.","startDate":1437868800,"revision":3,"events":[],"conditions":[{"display":"Partly Cloudy","tag":"partly-cloudy"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":89,"temperatureLow":69,"temperatureHighCelcius":32,"temperatureLowCelcius":21},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Hot then Rain Chances","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Omaha, Des Moines, Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, or St. Louis, most days will be dry and hot with temperatures above average. The end of this period will see an increase in the chance of showers and thunderstorms as the summer monsoon tries to shift east and a weak storm system comes out of the Rockies.This will be a good week to head to the Lake of the Ozarks or Branson, just keep an eye to the sky if you are there during the weekend.  Go to Weather2020.com, enter our long range forecasting contest with a monthly winner of a $100 Visa Gift Card, and join the LRC Forecast Experience blog to learn more about this breakthrough technology.","startDate":1438473600,"revision":2,"events":[],"conditions":[{"tag":"partly-cloudy","display":"Partly Cloudy"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":94,"temperatureLow":73,"temperatureHighCelcius":34,"temperatureLowCelcius":23},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Hot then Thunderstorms","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, St. Louis, Des Moines, or Omaha, the week will start hot and humid. Then a cold front and system will come east out of the Rockies. This will increase the chance of thunderstorms from west to east in all locations for a two to three day period. Temperatures this week will start above average, but drop to slightly below average. The best days to head to the lake will be early in the period.","startDate":1439078400,"revision":1,"events":[],"conditions":[{"display":"Partly Cloudy","tag":"partly-cloudy"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":93,"temperatureLow":73,"temperatureHighCelcius":34,"temperatureLowCelcius":23},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Thunderstorms Likely","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, St. Louis, Des Moines, or Omaha, there will be four to five days with chance of thunderstorms. Some areas could see heavy rain. Weather 2020 will be tracking two main systems and their associated cold fronts. Temperatures this week will run mostly below average. So this may not be the best week to head to the Lake of the Ozarks, Branson, or any other area lakes.","startDate":1439683200,"revision":1,"events":[],"conditions":[{"display":"Thunderstorm","tag":"thunderstorm"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":83,"temperatureLow":62,"temperatureHighCelcius":28,"temperatureLowCelcius":17},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Several Chances of Rain","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, Springfield, St. Louis, Des Moines, or Omaha, there will be chances of rain and thunderstorms four to five days this week. Flooding may be an issue, check back for updates. Temperatures this week will run mostly below to much below average. We are in the part of the pattern that we have termed the \"cold phase\" in this years LRC. This was the coldest part of the pattern during the winter, and brought the cool and wet weather in May and early June. This will be a challenging week to hit the pool or head to the lake.","startDate":1440288000,"revision":2,"events":[],"conditions":[{"tag":"thunderstorm","display":"Thunderstorm"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":77,"temperatureLow":56,"temperatureHighCelcius":25,"temperatureLowCelcius":13},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Good Weather Heading to Labor Day Weekend","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, St. Louis, Branson, Lake of the Ozarks, Des Moines, or Omaha, there will be a good chance of rain and thunderstorms for two or three days, mainly early in the period. Then a ridge moves in from the west, shutting off the rain and allowing temperatures to rise to above average. It looks like a good Labor Day weekend.","startDate":1440892800,"revision":2,"events":[],"conditions":[{"tag":"thunderstorm","display":"Thunderstorm"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":90,"temperatureLow":69,"temperatureHighCelcius":32,"temperatureLowCelcius":21},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Mostly Nice Weather","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, Springfield, St. Louis, Des Moines, or Omaha, most days will be dry with mostly above average temperatures. There will be one or two days with a chance of showers and thunderstorms. The rain will be caused by a weak cold front and associated system.  It looks like a good week to head to the Lake of the Ozarks or Branson. Labor Day looks to be dry and warm.","startDate":1441497600,"revision":2,"events":[],"conditions":[{"tag":"partly-cloudy","display":"Partly Cloudy"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":88,"temperatureLow":67,"temperatureHighCelcius":31,"temperatureLowCelcius":19},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Likely a Wet Week","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, Springfield, Branson, St. Louis, Des Moines, or Omaha, be prepared for rain four to five days this week. There will be a series of systems tracking in from the southwest with a possible tropical connection, followed by a cold front. This may not be the best week for outdoor activities. Temperatures will run near to below average.","startDate":1442102400,"revision":1,"events":[],"conditions":[{"display":"Thunderstorm","tag":"thunderstorm"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":75,"temperatureLow":54,"temperatureHighCelcius":24,"temperatureLowCelcius":12},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Very Warm and Thunderstorms","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, Springfield, St. Louis, Des Moines, or Omaha, there will be three or four days with chances of thunderstorms. This will be due to a mostly stalled front between I-70 and I-80 as small disturbances increase thunderstorm development along this front. These will not be all day events, so there will be many dry hours during the days with thunderstorms. The beginning of the period may see a wet system, possibly tropical in origin, affect southern Missouri. Temperatures will run mostly above average. This week will feature warm and humid weather with thunderstorms and may not be a great week to head to the Lake or Branson.","startDate":1442707200,"revision":1,"events":[],"conditions":[{"display":"Thunderstorm","tag":"thunderstorm"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":82,"temperatureLow":60,"temperatureHighCelcius":28,"temperatureLowCelcius":16},{"regionAffected":"Central Plains","headline":"Two Cold Fronts","forecastDesc":"If you have vacation or wedding plans this week in Dodge City, Wichita, Topeka, Kansas City, Columbia, Springfield, St. Louis, Des Moines and Omaha most days will be dry and comfortable with near average temperatures.  2-3 of the days will have chances of showers and thunderstorms as two cold fronts drop southeast.  Each front will bring a chance of rain for 1-2 days.  This looks like a good week to head to Branson or the Lake of the Ozarks.  Go to Weather2020.com, enter our long range forecasting contest with a monthly winner of a $100 Visa Gift Card, and join the LRC Forecast Experience blog to learn more about this breakthrough technology.","startDate":1443312000,"revision":0,"events":[],"conditions":[{"tag":"partly-cloudy","display":"Partly Cloudy"}],"forecastLengthInHours":168,"temperatureHigh":74,"temperatureLow":52,"temperatureHighCelcius":23,"temperatureLowCelcius":11}]

description: Weather2020 is the most popular long range weather forecast API available! Used by popular mobile apps like 1Weather, and already serving over 10 million forecasts a day, the Weather2020 long range weather forecasts give you something new and unique for your weather, travel or outdoor applications. Created by famed meteorologist Gary Lezak, our forecasts are powered by the most accurate long range weather model known as the LRC. For the first time ever, give your users a reliable and accurate long range weather forecast!
name: v1
